1778587172s:2291:"<p id="bkmrk-cdm-%28camu%29-is-a-tool">CDM (CAMU) is a tool to manage demand and capacity across the division by regulating departures and adjusting traffic patterns to prevent sector overload.</p>
<p id="bkmrk-how-to-start-cdm%3F">How to Start CDM?</p>
<ul id="bkmrk-when-loading-up-the-">
<li>When loading up the sector file (2602 and later), a CDM Airport Panel will appear. By default, you are put into the 'slave' role. Selecting the airports that you are providing top-down coverage for you will become a 'master' of the airport.</li>
</ul>
<p id="bkmrk-when-am-i-the-%27maste">When am I the 'master' or the 'slave'?</p>
<ul id="bkmrk-during-normal-operat">
<li>During normal operations, the 'master' of the airport should be the lowest position, e.g. Delivery. The master is the only user who has the functionality to edit CDM timings.</li>
</ul>
<p id="bkmrk-how-do-i-use-cdm%3F">How do I use CDM?</p>
<ul id="bkmrk-when-an-aircraft-cal">
<li>When an aircraft calls ready for push, the 'master' controller should left click the TOBT column in the Startup List to generate CDM times. The controller should then look at the TSAT time, and if it is within +/- 5 minutes of the current time, pushback (or handover to GMC) should be approved.</li>
</ul>
<p id="bkmrk-what-do-i-do-when-ha">What do I do when handing over from CLD to GMC?</p>
<ul id="bkmrk-whilst-operating-cld">
<li>Whilst operating CLD, and aircraft that is handed over from CLD to GMC should have their aircraft STS set to the 'S/UP' status.</li>
</ul>
<p id="bkmrk-what-happens-when-an">What happens when an aircraft misses their TSAT slot?
If an aircraft misses their slot, then the timings should simply be re-generated by left clicking the TOBT column. A flight that has missed their slot will be indicated with a red 'SUSP' message in the NET column.</p>
<p id="bkmrk-useful-commands%3A">Useful commands:</p>
<ul id="bkmrk-.cdm-panel---hides-t">
<li>.cdm panel - Hides the CDM panel</li>
<li>.cdm master/slave ICAO - Master, or slave an airport</li>
<li>.cdm atfcm - Shows the ATFCM list</li>
<li>.cdm refresh - Refresh the CDM plugin</li>
</ul>
